Adapted portions:

  internal/memory/service.go
      The two-method Service interface (AddSessionToMemory / SearchMemory),
      the Entry shape (id, author, timestamp, custom metadata), and the
      SearchRequest / SearchResponse pair are adapted from adk-go/memory.
      Locutus scopes entries by Namespace rather than user+app, uses a
      plain string for Content rather than genai.Content, and treats
      SearchRequest.Query as a case-insensitive substring predicate.

  internal/eval/evaluator.go, runner.go, llmjudge.go
      The Evaluator interface, the EvalCase / EvalMetric separation, and
      the LLM-as-judge pattern are adapted from google/adk-python's
      evaluation framework (src/google/adk/evaluation). Locutus drops
      ADK's EvalSet / Invocation abstractions (those assume a chat-turn
      runtime Locutus does not have) and keys the Runner's dispatch on
      spec.AssertionKind rather than evaluator names. The JSON output
      schema (passed / reasoning / confidence) is Locutus-native.

Governing decisions: DJ-077 (selective ADK adoption), DJ-078 (Locutus
serialization format and text/template policy).

